Setup Instructions:
===================

VIM Commands:
-------------

CTRL-n: NERDTreeToggle
CTRL-p: https://github.com/kien/ctrlp.vim

,<motion>: https://github.com/Lokaltog/vim-easymotion

,ev: Edit .vimrc

10,cc: comment 10 lines
10,cu: uncomment 10 lines

`,grf` git rebase fixup - replace all but first `pick` to `fixup`
`,fgrf` force git rebase fixup

`,grs` git rebase squash - replace all but first `pick` to `squash`
`,fgrs` force git rebase squash

ZSH Commands:
-------------

mk: mkdir and cd

csha: copy git SHA
cbn: copy git branch name
fsha <SHA>: find sha in

Direnv + iTerm2 Background Colors:
----------------------------------

Changes iTerm2 background color based on current directory.

Setup:
1. brew install direnv
2. Create ~/.config/direnv/direnv.toml:
   [global]
   hide_env_diff = true

   [whitelist]
   prefix = ["~/dev/vidu"]

3. Add .envrc to project directories:
   export ITERM_BGCOLOR="000033"  # blue

Color examples:
  000033 - blue
  330033 - purple
  003333 - teal
  330000 - red
